    "instructions": "Cut the onions in half from top to bottom, then slice them into thin strips. Sauté in oil and butter over low heat for 5 minutes. Add the drained tuna and sauté briefly. Mix in the curry and flour, cook briefly. Add the broth and fill with coconut milk. Let it simmer briefly, add the chopped pineapple (two slices or to taste) and season with salt, pepper, and a good splash of pineapple juice. Serve with rice.",
